00075 GUILoadThread::GUILoadThread(MFXInterThreadEventClient* mw,
00076                              MFXEventQue& eq, FXEX::FXThreadEvent& ev)
00077     : FXSingleEventThread(gFXApp, mw), myParent(mw), myEventQue(eq),
00078       myEventThrow(ev) {
00079     myErrorRetriever = new MsgRetrievingFunction<GUILoadThread>(this, &GUILoadThread::retrieveMessage, MsgHandler::MT_ERROR);
00080     myMessageRetriever = new MsgRetrievingFunction<GUILoadThread>(this, &GUILoadThread::retrieveMessage, MsgHandler::MT_MESSAGE);
00081     myWarningRetriever = new MsgRetrievingFunction<GUILoadThread>(this, &GUILoadThread::retrieveMessage, MsgHandler::MT_WARNING);
00082     MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->addRetriever(myErrorRetriever);
00083 }

00093 FXint
00094 GUILoadThread::run() {
00095     GUINet* net = 0;
00096     int simStartTime = 0;
00097     int simEndTime = 0;
00098     OptionsCont& oc = OptionsCont::getOptions();
00099 
00100     // within gui-based applications, nothing is reported to the console
00101     MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->report2cout(false);
00102     MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->report2cerr(false);
00103     MsgHandler::getWarningInstance()->report2cout(false);
00104     MsgHandler::getWarningInstance()->report2cerr(false);
00105     MsgHandler::getMessageInstance()->report2cout(false);
00106     MsgHandler::getMessageInstance()->report2cerr(false);
00107     // register message callbacks
00108     MsgHandler::getMessageInstance()->addRetriever(myMessageRetriever);
00109     MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->addRetriever(myErrorRetriever);
00110     MsgHandler::getWarningInstance()->addRetriever(myWarningRetriever);
00111 
00112     // try to load the given configuration
00113     if (!initOptions()) {
00114         // the options are not valid
00115         submitEndAndCleanup(net, simStartTime, simEndTime);
00116         return 0;
00117     }
00118     MsgHandler::initOutputOptions(true);
00119     if (!MSFrame::checkOptions()) {
00120         // the options are not valid
00121         MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->inform("Quitting (on error).", false);
00122         submitEndAndCleanup(net, simStartTime, simEndTime);
00123         return 0;
00124     }
00125 
00126     RandHelper::initRandGlobal();
00127     // try to load
00128     MSFrame::setMSGlobals(oc);
00129 #ifdef HAVE_MESOSIM
00130     GUIVisualizationSettings::UseMesoSim = MSGlobals::gUseMesoSim;
00131     if (MSGlobals::gUseMesoSim) {
00132         net = new GUINet(new MEVehicleControl(), new GUIEventControl(),
00133                          new GUIEventControl(), new GUIEventControl());
00134     } else {
00135 #endif
00136         net = new GUINet(new GUIVehicleControl(), new GUIEventControl(),
00137                          new GUIEventControl(), new GUIEventControl());
00138 #ifdef HAVE_MESOSIM
00139     }
00140 #endif
00141     GUIEdgeControlBuilder* eb = new GUIEdgeControlBuilder();
00142     GUIDetectorBuilder db(*net);
00143     NLJunctionControlBuilder jb(*net, db);
00144     GUITriggerBuilder tb;
00145     NLHandler handler("", *net, db, tb, *eb, jb);
00146     tb.setHandler(&handler);
00147     NLBuilder builder(oc, *net, *eb, jb, db, handler);
00148     try {
00149         MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->clear();
00150         MsgHandler::getWarningInstance()->clear();
00151         MsgHandler::getMessageInstance()->clear();
00152         if (!builder.build()) {
00153             throw ProcessError();
00154         } else {
00155             net->initGUIStructures();
00156             simStartTime = string2time(oc.getString("begin"));
00157             simEndTime = string2time(oc.getString("end"));
00158         }
00159     } catch (ProcessError& e) {
00160         if (std::string(e.what()) != std::string("Process Error") && std::string(e.what()) != std::string("")) {
00161             WRITE_ERROR(e.what());
00162         }
00163         MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->inform("Quitting (on error).", false);
00164         delete net;
00165         net = 0;
00166 #ifndef _DEBUG
00167     } catch (std::exception& e) {
00168         WRITE_ERROR(e.what());
00169         delete net;
00170         net = 0;
00171 #endif
00172     }
00173     if (net == 0) {
00174         MSNet::clearAll();
00175     }
00176     delete eb;
00177     submitEndAndCleanup(net, simStartTime, simEndTime);
00178     return 0;
00179 }

00183 void
00184 GUILoadThread::submitEndAndCleanup(GUINet* net,
00185                                    SUMOTime simStartTime,
00186                                    SUMOTime simEndTime) {
00187     // remove message callbacks
00188     MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->removeRetriever(myErrorRetriever);
00189     MsgHandler::getWarningInstance()->removeRetriever(myWarningRetriever);
00190     MsgHandler::getMessageInstance()->removeRetriever(myMessageRetriever);
00191     // inform parent about the process
00192     GUIEvent* e = new GUIEvent_SimulationLoaded(net, simStartTime, simEndTime, myFile,
00193             OptionsCont::getOptions().getString("gui-settings-file"));
00194     myEventQue.add(e);
00195     myEventThrow.signal();
00196 }

00199 bool
00200 GUILoadThread::initOptions() {
00201     try {
00202         OptionsCont& oc = OptionsCont::getOptions();
00203         oc.clear();
00204         MSFrame::fillOptions();
00205         if (myFile != "") {
00206             if (myLoadNet) {
00207                 oc.set("net-file", myFile);
00208             } else {
00209                 oc.set("configuration-file", myFile);
00210             }
00211             OptionsIO::getOptions(true, 1, 0);
00212         } else {
00213             OptionsIO::getOptions(true);
00214         }
00215         return true;
00216     } catch (ProcessError& e) {
00217         if (std::string(e.what()) != std::string("Process Error") && std::string(e.what()) != std::string("")) {
00218             WRITE_ERROR(e.what());
00219         }
00220         MsgHandler::getErrorInstance()->inform("Quitting (on error).", false);
00221     }
00222     return false;
00223 }
